      "FacilityID": 1000010609,
      "SummaryText": "The Town of Mooresville Water Treatment Facility has an on-going Chlorine Safety Program that maintains complinace with NCDOL OSHA, as well as, EPA standards. We employ the usage of Chlorine Gas as our disinfection teatment process. Since our last RMP submission, we have undergone courteousy inspections from NCDOL OSHA, as well as, hiring a full-time Risk Manager within the city. These factors have helpled us raise the bar in regards to our ability to provide a safe working environment for our employees, and manitain a safer world for our community. We take seriously the task of managing Chlorine Gas and its potential hazards. We train/test our employees ever year, as we update our PSM/Chlorine Gas program. We've initiated a Mechanical Integity plan, as well as, an evolving SOP. We will continue to do manage our Chlorine Safety program and EDUCATE our employees is ALL areas regarding the potential hazards of Chlorine Gas.\n\nALARM/MUSTER/EVACUATE/911"
    }
